      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;definition-of-vector-space&#34;&gt;Definition of Vector Space&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-1-double-additive-inverse&#34;&gt;Exercise 1: Double Additive Inverse&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prove that $ -(-v) = v $ for every $ v \in V $, where $ V $ is a vector space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-2-zero-product-property&#34;&gt;Exercise 2: Zero Product Property&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suppose $ a \in \mathbb{F} $ (a field), $ v \in V $, and $ av = 0 $. Prove that $ a = 0 $ or $ v = 0 $.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-3-unique-solution-to-vector-equation&#34;&gt;Exercise 3: Unique Solution to Vector Equation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suppose $ v, w \in V $. Explain why there exists a unique $ x \in V $ such that $ v + 3x = w $.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
